   1         0                            ;
   2         0                            ;   call.asm -- CALL/RET, STM/LDM, XCH, ST, PUSH/POP, BR
   3         0                            ;
   4         0                            ;   Covers BR (via bare label), CALL (via bare label AND via /abs),
   5         0                            ;   STM (MOVEM src,ea), LDM (MOVEM ea,dst), XCH (EXG/SWAP), ST, PUSH
   6         0                            ;   and POP, and all three return variants.
   7         0                            ;
   8         0                            ;   The bare-label form of BR / CALL was broken in the 1990 code:
   9         0                            ;   Type 25 routed non-immediate operands to Type 15 (JMP/JSR), whose
  10         0                            ;   CalcEA requires an Absolute-typed operand, but labels are Relative.
  11         0                            ;   The port fixed this by routing Dir / Rel operands to Type 11 — the
  12         0                            ;   same Bcc encoder the conditional variants use — and leaving Abs /
  13         0                            ;   Ind operands to Type 15.  This fixture exercises both paths.
  14         0                            ;
